                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d383">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Powell</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-12-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 6, 1899</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 384.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have to acknowledge the receipt of your No.
                    659, of the 14th ultimo, relative to the right of asylum in Haiti. In reply I
                    have to say that in view of the peculiar situation in that Republic and the
                    varying circumstances of each case the only safe course would seem to be to
                    bring all the facts to the immediate attention of the Department and await its
                    instructions.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
